ZH: 铁路是一种重要的交通工具。
EN: Railways are an important mode of transportation.

ZH: 这条铁路连接了两个大城市。
EN: This railway connects two major cities.

ZH: 铁路运输可以快速便捷地到达目的地。
EN: Railway transport can quickly and conveniently reach the destination.

ZH: 我们乘坐铁路去旅行。
EN: We travel by rail.

ZH: 铁路系统可以促进经济发展。
EN: Railway systems can promote economic development.

ZH: 这个城市正在修建一条新的铁路线。
EN: The city is building a new railway line.

ZH: 铁路工程需要大量的资金和人力。
EN: Railway projects require a lot of funds and manpower.

ZH: 我们的国家有着发达的铁路网络。
EN: Our country has a developed railway network.

ZH: 铁路工人在寒冷的天气里工作很辛苦。
EN: Railway workers work hard in the cold weather.

ZH: 铁路是一种环保的交通方式。
EN: Railways are an environmentally friendly mode of transportation.

ZH: 我们计划在未来几年内修建更多的高铁。
EN: We plan to build more high-speed railways in the coming years.

ZH: 铁路系统对于货物运输也非常重要。
EN: Railway systems are also crucial for transporting goods.

ZH: 坐火车比开车更省钱。
EN: Taking the train is cheaper than driving.

ZH: 我们正在采取措施提高铁路的安全性。
EN: We are taking measures to improve the safety of railways.

ZH: 铁路可以提高交通运输的效率。
EN: Railways can improve the efficiency of transportation.

ZH: 这条铁路线已经存在了超过一百年。
EN: This railway line has been in existence for over a hundred years.

ZH: 铁路的建设需要考虑周围环境。
EN: The construction of railways needs to consider the surrounding environment.

ZH: 铁路旅行给人带来了很多美好的回忆。
EN: Railway travel brings many wonderful memories to people.

ZH: 铁路对于连接城市和农村地区起到了关键作用。
EN: Railways play a key role in connecting urban and rural areas.

ZH: 铁路改变了人们的生活方式。
EN: Railways have changed people's way of life.
